SENATE BILL No. 246
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning
criminal law and procedure.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 33-41-1-5 IS AMENDED TO READ AS
2 FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 5. (a) If requested to do
3 so, an official reporter shall furnish to either party in a cause a
4 transcript of all or any part of the proceedings required by the reporter
5 to be taken or noted, including all documentary evidence.
6 (b) An official reporter shall furnish a typewritten or printed
7 transcript described in subsection (a) as soon after being requested to
8 do so as practicable.
9 (c) The reporter shall certify that the transcript contains all the
10 evidence given in the cause.
11 (d) The reporter may require payment for a transcript, or that the
12 payment be satisfactorily secured, before the reporter proceeds to do
13 the required work.
14 (e) In a criminal action, the official reporter shall comply with
15 the requirements for redaction under IC 35-32-4.
16 SECTION 2. IC 35-32-4 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE AS
17 A NEW CHAPTER TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY
2026 IN 246—LS 7110/DI 106

2
1 1, 2026]:
2 Chapter 4. References to Child Victims and Witnesses
3 Sec. 1. This chapter applies only to a criminal action.
4 Sec. 2. In any document filed or submitted in a criminal action,
5 the following information must be redacted:
6 (1) A reference to the name of a child victim or a child
7 witness.
8 (2) A reference to the name of a person whose name is not
9 required to be redacted under subdivision (1), if the reference
10 to the name could be used to identify a child whose name is
11 required to be redacted under subdivision (1).
12 Sec. 3. The name of a person whose name is required to be
13 redacted under this chapter must be replaced with a descriptive
14 anonymous designator, such as "Child Witness No. 1" or
15 "Passenger". Initials or references to familial relationships may
16 not be used.
17 Sec. 4. If a reference to an unredacted name is necessary for the
18 resolution of the criminal action, any document containing the
19 unredacted name shall be filed as a separate confidential document
20 in accordance with Rule 5 of the Indiana Rules on Access to Court
21 Records.
